APPLEVIRTUALPLATFORMHIDBRIDGE(8)                         System Manager's Manual

NAME
     AppleVirtualPlatformHIDBridge â€“ Bridge HID services from a Virtualization
     host

SYNOPSIS
     AppleVirtualPlatformHIDBridge takes no arguments, and users should not
                                   launch it manually.

DESCRIPTION
     When macOS is running as a guest operating system in a virtual machine
     created by the Virtualization framework and configured with an
     AppleVirtualPlatformHIDBridge device, AppleVirtualPlatformHIDBridge
     instantiates and manages virtual input devices on behalf of the host.

HISTORY
     AppleVirtualPlatformHIDBridge first appeared in macOS 13.

